[1]
Date: Tue, 15 Mar 2005
From: A-Lan Banks <A-Lan.Banks@thomson.com>
Source: Yonhap News, South Korea, 15 Mar 2005 [edited]
<http://english.yna.co.kr/Engnews/20050315/310000000020050315164940E3.html>


Outbreak of Bird Influenza Reported in North Korea: Source
----------------------------------------------------------
Thousands of chickens perished in North Korea about a month ago after
a suspected case of bird influenza hit the communist country for the
1st time, a source in Beijing said Tuesday [15 Mar 2005].

The informed source said the outbreak occurred at Hadang, the North's
main chicken factory in Pyongyang, prompting authorities there to
come up with emergency measures to stem the spread of the disease.

--
